I said in a previous thread that I thought I should actually comment more on the stories I read, I'll go through everything in the OP I read.
Sorry if I have to say more on some than on others, it might've been a while since I read it or I was dead tired when I did.

>Kash'Gons Chronicles
This story is written as a report of events, this allows it to speed through events that would take pages in other stories in just a couple sentences. I still enjoyed it greatly until chapter 14, which gave me the impression the waifur Rayla wouldn't want to marry any outsiders that don't have "a connection to the land".

The (I'll call it) 2nd part with the MC in the desert had another completely different culture, which wasn't uninteresting, but I greatly prefered the forest setting, so I already don't remember much of it.
At the end the MC is forced to leave them again and I guess enter a completely different culture yet again.
It's a nice piece of writing to introduce us to the world, I'd read something more traditional that takes place in the same world too.

>Emotional Support Human
A very unique setting starring the neet wolf from those funny japanese youtube videos our local translate anon is working so hard on.
Ookami the neet wolf has requested the help of the ESH (emotional support human) to help with her anxiety, of course she has second thoughts the moment the human actually arrives.
The story feels realistic with Ookami's problems and how Anon is helping her.
Therapy is a long journey and there are only two chapters so far, it's already heartwarming to see her make little improvements to her current situation.
There are some hints for potential romance, but as a profesional, Anon still wants to avoid her falling for him at this point.
